  • Classes in de.dedede.model.persistence.exceptions used by de.dedede.model.logic.managedbeans 
    Class Description
    MaxConnectionsException
    This checked exception is used for situations in which a connection object is requested from the connection pool while all connections are already in use.
  • Classes in de.dedede.model.persistence.exceptions used by de.dedede.model.persistence.daos 
    Class Description
    EntityInstanceDoesNotExistException
    This checked exception describes situations in which an entity, as represented by a data entry, is absent from the data store.
    EntityInstanceNotUniqueException
    This checked exception describes situations in which the creation of an entity is attempted with an ID, that is already associated with another entity in the same data store.
  • Classes in de.dedede.model.persistence.exceptions used by de.dedede.model.persistence.util 
    Class Description
    LostConnectionException
    This checked exception is used for situations in which a connection object from the connection pool can no longer be used to execute data queries.
    MaxConnectionsException
    This checked exception is used for situations in which a connection object is requested from the connection pool while all connections are already in use.
